<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="106" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[189,310,1155,1181]" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" pageId="32" pageNumber="106">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="32" pageNumber="106" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1155,1181]" pageId="32" pageNumber="106">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[187,1399,1202,1369]" pageId="32" pageNumber="106">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1927" box="[477,631,1202,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaprensis">
<emphasis box="[477,631,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="106">S. chaprensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bluthgen" authorityYear="1924" box="[685,834,1202,1228]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Sphecodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simlaensis">
<emphasis box="[685,834,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="106">S. simlaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing similar shape and sculpture of the body, including weakly developed antennal tyloids, a densely punctate mesoscutum and scarcely punctate metasomal terga, but differs from these species by having longer antennae with flagellomeres (from F3 onward) ca 1.3 times as long as wide (vs 1.1–1.2) and the shape of the gonostylus without a membranous part.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
